# NDH Stability Geometry Manifold — Basin Topology Definition
# Location: /NDH/Manifold/Stability/Geometry/BasinTopology.def
# Purpose:
#   Define the structural topology of stability basins within the NDH manifold.
#   BasinTopology describes attractor layout, curvature class, boundary
#   transitions, and basin geometry used by BasinEntry, BasinFlow, and
#   Serenity.bsfn.

[Header]
Version = 1.0
Manifold = Stability
Component = BasinTopology
Boundary = NonDual
Status = Active

[Inputs]
StateVector            # current manifold position
CurvatureMap           # local curvature tensor
EnergyProfile          # energy distribution influencing topology
ResonanceProfile       # oscillatory amplitudes affecting basin shape

[Outputs]
TopologyClass          # classification of basin geometry
AttractorMap           # attractor layout within the basin
BoundarySet            # boundary conditions for basin transitions
TopologySignature      # canonical signature for routing

[Function BasinTopology.Compute]

# 1. Determine TopologyClass
TopologyClass = ClassifyTopology(
    curvature = CurvatureMap.LocalCurvature,
    energy    = EnergyProfile,
    resonance = ResonanceProfile
)

# 2. Generate AttractorMap
AttractorMap = ComputeAttractors(
    topology  = TopologyClass,
    curvature = CurvatureMap.LocalCurvature
)

# 3. Compute BoundarySet
BoundarySet = ComputeBoundaries(
    topology  = TopologyClass,
    gradient  = CurvatureMap.CurvatureGradient
)

# 4. Generate TopologySignature
TopologySignature = HashSignature(
    topology  = TopologyClass,
    attractor = AttractorMap,
    boundary  = BoundarySet
)

Return TopologyClass, AttractorMap, BoundarySet, TopologySignature

[Notes]
- BasinTopology defines the structural geometry of Serenity and other basins.
- BasinEntry uses topology implicitly through curvature and drift.
- BasinFlow uses topology to shape flow vectors.
- Serenity.bsfn uses topology to determine relaxation behavior.
- Legacy constructs must never call BasinTopology directly.

[EndOfFile]
